summary: The first thing Rhodes says when he finds Tony after he escapes in the first Iron Man is, “How was the fun-vee?” Not “How are...
body:
The first thing Rhodes says when he finds Tony after he escapes in the first Iron Man is, “How was the fun-vee?” Not “How are you?” or “Thank goodness!” but a joke and it’s perfect, because consider this: Tony Stark is someone who genuinely loves to laugh and snark and joke and he surrounds himself with people who will banter with him. But he’s been in a cave and under pressure and while Yinsen is kind, Tony hasn’t truly laughed in what feels like forever. Then finally, finally Rhodes finds Tony and the very first thing he says - because he knows his friend so, so well - is a joke, the first joke Tony has heard in a long time, and you can just see him collapse and truly laugh for the first time in ages when Rhodes pulls him in for a hug.

(The first thing out of Pepper’s mouth is also something she knows he’ll think is funny.)
